cs.MA, cs.MKT, cs.SI, cs.CE, cs.CR

The paper investigates the impact of daily deals on small businesses, which involves analyzing data and modeling correlations between various factors. This suggests that the paper could fall under multiple sub-categories, including cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) for analyzing the behavior of businesses, cs.MKT (Marketing) for studying the impact of daily deals on the market, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) for examining the use of email and social networks in daily deal promotions, cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) for modeling correlations between factors, and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) for potentially discussing the security of daily deal transactions.
